{
  "texts": [
    "We adapt the BP-OSD 36,65,66 to the circuit noise model.",
    "This involves both an offline and online stage.",
    "In the offline stage, we take as input the syndrome measurement circuit and the error rate p. For every distinct single fault, we simulate the circuit efficiently using the stabilizer formalism, tracking the probability of the fault, the syndrome observed, and a final ideal syndrome.",
    "We also record in each case the logical syndrome, which indicates the logical operators anticommuting with the final error.",
    "In the online stage, we take a syndrome instance and determine a likely set of faults that occurred."
  ]
}